This will free up disk space on C:, which presumably was the idea in the first place.\n</li><li> Keep the mail folders on the D: drive.\n</li><li> Delete any orphan files you may have copied over manually to the D: drive, e.g. like the address books.\n</li></ul>\n<p>You may want to do this while Thunderbird is closed, just in case.                 "content"[0;37m => [0m[0;33m"<p>First, you can create a screenshot and upload with a response. There is a button at bottom of response section for that.\n</p><p>Second, for threading: \nHere is official documentation: <a href=\"https://support.mozilla.org/en-US/kb/message-threading-thunderbird\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://support.mozilla.org/en-US/kb/message-threading-thunderbird</a> \n</p><p><strong>FOR NEW FOLDERS</strong> \nTo change default for *new* folders, In config editor, you can change default that applies to NEW folders you set up:\nmailnews.default_view_flags      0 =unthreaded  \n</p><p>Config editor is available at Tools&gt;settings&gt;general and scroll to bottom right. \n</p><pre> ------------\n</pre>\n<p><strong>FOR EXISTING FOLDERS</strong>\t\nThese steps may help: \nTo set many *existing* folders, follow these steps:\nThis must be done on an account by account basis.\n</p>\n<ol><li> select table view  - the icon just to right of 'quick filter' button above message list pane\n</li><li>  select a message folder and apply all desired attributes - View&gt;sort by from menu bar (if not shown, click alt key)\n</li><li>  click the icon at right side of column display in message list pane\n</li><li>  select the entry near bottom 'Apply current view to...'\n</li><li>  highlight 'folder and children'\n</li><li> move mouse left to see account name and move left again to display all account folders. Now CLICK. a small menu will appear to confirm setting all folders within that account.\n</li></ol>\n<p>I did a simple (okay, crude) video at <a href=\"https://davidkirk.org/SettingDefaultFolderView.mp4\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://davidkirk.org/SettingDefaultFolderView.mp4</a>\n</p><p><strong>FOR FUTURE INSTALLATIONS</strong>\nALSO, for future installations of Thunderbird, \n- create a simple text file with name of user.js with these lines: \n</p><pre>    // Set default threading to UNthreaded  ###   &lt;== this line is optional, just for documentation\n    user_pref(\"mailnews.default_view_flags\", 0);\n</pre>\n<p>- install Thunderbird and exit prior to setting up accounts\t \n- copy the user.js file into the profile\n- now, when you start Thunderbird, unthreading will be the default. Problem solved.\n</p>"[0m,
